<br>
I am therefore responsible for what ensued.<br>
<br>
It is my belief that Argnoth was righteously upset for being saddled with poor report due to mistaken identity.<br>
<br>
Argnoth, please accept my apology.  Although a mix-up like this is an honest misunderstanding, I completely understand the indignation it put you through.<br>
<br>
Furthermore, when I had a slot open for Argnoth again, the raid was called due to lack of critical mass.<br>
<br>
Argnoth, I have informed our guild council to make space for you on our next open-invite outing which you may have interest in.  Please accept this in token of our good faith, and feel free to claim it at any time.<br>
<br>
I'd like to give special thanks to Vivvia of Oracles of Fate and our own Boddkin Brandywine, XO of Vivix Protectorate for quickly and diplomatically getting to the bottom of the mistaken identity and clearing it up.  I was busy leading the raid, but they kept me in the loop, got to the bottom of it, laid the facts out, and showed us our error with dignity and class.  Again, my thanks to you both.  You have shown us that goodwill and diplomacy in our EMarr community CAN in fact prevail if we have the integrity and presence of mind to let it.<br>
<br>
Safe journeys to you,<br>
